          </p><p>Donation (please "Send", not "Request"):=20
    <a href=3D"https://paypal.me/ahpDonation">paypal.me/ahpDonation</a></p>=
<h2>Multi-criteria Decision Making Using the Analytic Hierarchy Process</h2=
><div class=3D"entry-content"><p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        This free <b>web based AHP solution</b> is a suppor=
ting=20
                        tool for decision making processes.
                        The programs can be helpful in your daily work for =
simple decision problems and also support complex=20
                        decision making problems. Participate in a group se=
ssion and try a=20
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/participate-in-an-ahp-=
group-session-ahp-practical-example/">practical example</a>.=20
                        Download the <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/docs/=
BPMSG-AHP-OS-QuickReference.pdf" target=3D"_blank">quick reference guide</a=
>=20
                        or the <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/docs/BPMSG-=
AHP-OS.pdf" target=3D"_blank">AHP-OS manual</a>.=20
                        For full functionality you need to login. Please <a=
 href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/includes/login/do/do-register.php">register<=
/a>=20
                        as new user, if you don't have an account yet. It's=
 all free!
                        </p></div><ol style=3D"line-height:150%;">
                        <li><span style=3D"cursor:help;" title=3D"Manage co=
mplete AHP projects and group sessions. You need to be a registered user an=
d login.">
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-session-admin.=
php">My AHP Projects</a></span></li>
                        <li><span style=3D"cursor:help;" title=3D"The AHP p=
riority calculator calculates priorities or weights for a set of criteria b=
ased on pairwise comparisons.">
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-calc.php">AHP =
Priority Calculator</a></span></li>
                        <li><span style=3D"cursor:help;" title=3D"Handle co=
mplete decision problems under AHP. Define a hierarchy of criteria and eval=
uate alternatives.">
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-hierarchy.php"=
>AHP Hierarchies</a></span></li>
                        <li><span style=3D"cursor:help;" title=3D"Participa=
te in an AHP group sessions to evaluate criteria or alternatives as a membe=
r of a group">
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-hiergini.php">=
AHP Group Session</a></span></li>
                        <li><span style=3D"cursor:help;" title=3D"Analyze g=
roup consensus">
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-cluster.php">G=
roup Consensus Cluster Analysis</a></span>=20
                        <small>(experimental)</small></li>
                        </ol><p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        For programs 2 and 3 you can export the results as =
csv files (comma separated values) for further=20
                        processing in excel.</p><p style=3D"text-align:just=
ify;">
                        <b>For terms of use please see our </b>=20
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/about/user-agreement-a=
nd-privacy-policy/">
                        user agreement and privacy policy.</a></p><p style=
=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        If you like the program, <span class=3D"err">please=
 help and consider a=20
                        <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-news.php">dona=
tion</a> to maintain the website</span>.</p><p><b>For your work please cite=
:</b><br>
                        <code>Goepel, K.D. (2018). Implementation of an Onl=
ine Software Tool for the Analytic Hierarchy=20
                        Process (AHP-OS). <i>International Journal of the A=
nalytic Hierarchy Process</i>, Vol. 10 Issue 3 2018, pp 469-487,
                        <br><a href=3D"https://doi.org/10.13033/ijahp.v10i3=
.590">https://doi.org/10.13033/ijahp.v10i3.590</a>
                        </code></p><h3>Introduction</h3>
                        <div style=3D"display:inline;">
                        <img src=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/images/AHP-icon-1=
50x150.png" alt=3D"AHP" style=3D"float: left; height:15%; width:15%; paddin=
g:5px;">
                        </div><div class=3D"entry-summary"><p style=3D"text=
-align:justify;">
                        AHP stands for <i>Analytic Hierarchy Process</i>. I=
t is a method to support=20
                        multi-criteria decision making, and was originally =
developed by Prof. Thomas L. Saaty. AHP derives=20
                        <i>ratio scales</i> from paired comparisons of crit=
eria, and allows for some small inconsistencies in=20
                        judgments. Inputs can be actual measurements, but a=
lso subjective opinions. As a result,=20
                        <i>priorities</i> (weightings) and a <i>consistency=
 ratio</i> will be calculated.
                        Internationally AHP is used in a wide range of appl=
ications, for example for the evaluation=20
                        of suppliers, in project management, in the hiring =
process or the evaluation of company performance. </p></div>    <div style=
=3D"display:block;clear:both;">
                        <h3>Benefits of AHP</h3>
                        <p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        Using AHP as a supporting tool for decision making =
will help to=20
                        gain a <i>better insight in complex decision proble=
ms</i>. As you need to structure the problem as a=20
                        hierarchy, it forces you to think through the probl=
em, consider possible decision criteria and select=20
                        the most significant criteria with respect to the d=
ecision objective. Using pairwise comparisons=20
                        helps to discover and correct logical inconsistenci=
es. The method also allows to "translate"=20
                        subjective opinions, such as preferences or feeling=
s, into measurable numeric relations.=20
                        AHP helps to makes decisions in a more rational way=
 and to make them more transparent and=20
                        better understandable.
                        </p>    <h3>Method</h3>
                        <p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        Mathematically the method is based on the solution =
of=20
                        an Eigenvalue problem. The results of the pair-wise=
 comparisons are arranged in a matrix.=20
                        The first (dominant) normalized right Eigen vector =
of the matrix gives the ratio scale (weighting), the=20
                        Eigenvalue determines the consistency ratio.
                        </p>    <h3>AHP Examples</h3>
                        <p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        In order to make the method easier to understand, a=
nd to show the=20
                        wide range of possible applications, we give some <=
a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/ahp/ahp-examples.php">examples</a>=20
                        for different decision hierarchies.
                        </p>
                        <p style=3D"text-align:justify;">
                        A simple introduction=20
                        to the method is given <a href=3D"https://bpmsg.com=
/ahp/docs/AHP-articel.Goepel.en.pdf" target=3D"_blank">here</a>.
                        </p></div><div style=3D"clear:both;"><h2>Contact an=
d Feedback</h2><p>
                        Please feel free to leave a <a href=3D"https://bpms=
g.com/feedback/#reply-title">comment</a>.</p><small>The AHP-OS package is r=
ealized in php and available from the author=20
        on <a href=3D"https://github.com/bpmsg/ahp-os" target=3D"_blank">Gi=
thub</a>.</small></div><div style=3D"display: inline; font-size: small;">
	AHP-OS author:=20
	<span class=3D"author vcard">
		<span class=3D"fn"> Klaus D. Goepel</span>,=20
		<span class=3D"org">BPMSG</span>.
		<a class=3D"url" href=3D"https://bpmsg.com/contact-form/;%20?%3E">Contact=
</a>		<span class=3D"updated" title=3D"">
		Last update: Aug 16, 2024</span>=20
